{
  "texts": [
    "The last few layers of the ResNet model, responsible for the final classification, are replaced with new layers trained on the biomedical dataset.",
    "The new layers learn the specific features of the biomedical images and improve classification accuracy.",
    "This approach has been used in various biomedical image classification tasks, such as breast cancer detection, brain tumor segmentation, and lung nodule detection, and has shown promising results in improving the accuracy of classification compared to traditional ML algorithms [65].",
    "Graph embedding using GCN for protein interaction predictionProteins interact with each other in complex ways to perform vital biological functions.",
    "The prediction of novel protein interactions is important for understanding cellular processes and developing new drugs."
  ]
}